4h6.title: Normal subgroup
4h6.clickbait: Normal subgroups are subgroups which are in some sense "the same from all points of view".
4h6.text:
A *normal subgroup* $N$ of group $G$ is one which is closed under [4gk conjugation]: for all $h \in G$, it is the case that $\{ h n h^{-1} : n \in N \} = N$.
In shorter form, $hNh^{-1} = N$.

Since [4gk conjugacy is equivalent to "changing the worldview], a normal subgroup is one which "looks the same from the point of view of every element of $G$".

A subgroup of $G$ is normal if and only if it is the [49y kernel] of some [47t] from $G$ to some group $H$. ([4h7 Proof.])
